"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc() function returns an array of sinc values, but the sinc function is defined as sinc(x) = sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) if x != 0 and sinc(0) = 1. The sinc function has floating point values for most inputs, but the code is trying to cast the result to int64, which will truncate the decimal part and lead to incorrect results. The correct way is to keep the result as a floating point array.\", \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sinc_result = np.sinc(original_data).astype(original_data.dtype)\\n---\\n> sinc_result = np.sinc(original_data)\\n\"}"